  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Write a program to find minimum number of swaps required to gather all elements less than or equals to k.\n\nFor example:\n\n  The given array is\n\n  arr[]={2,1,5,6,3},k=3\n\n  Output: 1\n\n\n\nExplanation: To bring elements 2,1,3 together , swap elements '5' with '3' such that final array will be arr[]={2,1,3,6,5}\n\nThe given array is:2 7 9 5 8 7 4\n\nk=5\n\nThe minimum swap required is:2",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= N <= 100",
      "1 <= arr[i] <= 1000",
      "1 <=K <= max(arr)"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line has an integer N represents the size of the array.\n\nSecond line contains the N values seperated by space.\n\nThird line contains an integer K.",
    "outputFormat": "Print the count.",
